# Company Data & Research Standards

Full detail: `.playbook/11_COMPANY_SCHEMA.md`, `.playbook/07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md`, `archive/README.md`.

- Evidence over assumption. Every factual claim needs a traceable source (company's own careers page/case study >
  vendor-confirmed > reputable secondary > inference, in that priority order).
- **Complete field pass** on every new or refreshed company — do not publish partial research (careers-only, then
  products later, then roles later). Use the field table in `07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md`.
- Public rows need non-empty `evidence` and `hiringEvidence` (http URLs). Listing implies AEM usage — do not add
  companies that do not use AEM.
- Set `verifiedAt` whenever evidence or hiring signal is checked.
- Required `ownerVerified`: set **`false`** on any agent-added or materially rewritten row. Only the project owner
  sets `true` after manual check. Do not invent `true` for new companies.
- Optional `hiringActive`: frequent/general hiring pattern only — **not** “openings exist right now”. Omit until
  the owner confirms. Do not set from a single job posting. Site disclaimer must keep this distinction clear.
- Optional `ownerPreferred`: owner recommendation (pay / growth / quality). Omit unless the owner explicitly marks
  it; put a short why in `notes`. Not the same as `hiringActive` or `priority`.
- Encode Adobe stack only in `products` (short codes). Do not reintroduce per-product boolean flags.
- Set `priority` using the hiring-cadence rubric in `07_RESEARCH_GUIDE.md` (not brand awards). Cap BuiltWith-only
  rows at 6 until Tier-1/2 evidence upgrades them.
- `roles` must match titles this employer uses (AEM / DXP / Software / Sr …) — no shared boilerplate lists.
- Optional `signals` (ratings) only when sourced with `source` + `asOf` — never invent scores for empty rows.
- **Published DB only:** `data/companies.json`. Do not introduce a second live company JSON.
- Files under `archive/research/md/` and `archive/companies/` are historical (DR-017) — never copy them into
  `data/companies.json` as confirmed fact without re-verification.
- No duplicate company entries without reconciling conflicting details into one record.
- After material edits: `node scripts/verify-companies.js`.
